FOOTBALL heroes are helping Show Racism the Red Card at the kick-off of a fortnight of action. Action kicks off to show racism the red card FOOTBALL heroes are helping Show Racism the Red Card at the kick-off of a fortnight of action.Pundit Chick Young, referee Garry Gentils and former footballer Kenny Brannigan launched the call for action, from today until October 23.The charity is urging all sections of communities to celebrate diversity and tackle racism.SPFL players will wear strips carrying Show Racism and Bigotry the Red card sticker transfers at all games during the fortnight.Matches will have anti-racist tannoy announcements and there will be articles in match programmes and on club websites.There will also be anti-racism stadium hoardings and players will wear Show Racism the Red Card T-shirts at training.Picture: Nick Ponty 